### Obtener links sin token
GET http://192.168.1.40:3000/links

### Obtener links con token
### Crear un nuevo link (protegido)

POST http://192.168.1.40:3000/links
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{loginUser.response.body.token}}

{
  "title": "Mi Portafolio",
  "url": "https://mi-portafolio.com"
}

### ---

### Obtener mis links (protegido)
GET http://192.168.1.40:3000/links
Authorization: Bearer {{loginUser.response.body.token}}

### ------------------
### TEST COMPLETO DE CRUD
### ------------------

# Primero, crea un link para tener un ID
# @name createForTest
POST http://192.168.1.40:3000/links
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{loginUser.response.body.token}}

{
  "title": "Link para borrar",
  "url": "https://google.com"
}

### ---

# Ahora, usa el ID de la respuesta de arriba para actualizarlo
# Reemplaza <ID_DEL_LINK_CREADO> con el ID real
@linkId = {{createForTest.response.body.id}}

PUT http://192.168.1.40:3000/links/{{linkId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{loginUser.response.body.token}}

{
  "title": "Link ACTUALIZADO",
  "url": "https://bing.com"
}

### ---

# Finalmente, borra ese mismo link
DELETE http://192.168.1.40:3000/links/{{linkId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{loginUser.response.body.token}}

